commit_list.message:
Unset the number string in the zero filled number list

This is necessary because the wrong `index` will be selected if a 
submitted number has identical groups.

For example 123123 would be converted to [‘123’,’123] and getting the
index for ‘123’ would always return 0 if the first item wasn’t set to 
None once it had been processed.
commit_list.repo_description: Python class for converting positive integers to a textual representation in British English

commit_list.message:
Iterate over groups of numbers converting them to words

Pass each group of numbers to _number_to_word_list() with any required
suffix (determined by looking up suffix in `LARGE_NUMBERS`) then create
a sentence by joining returned list of words with a space character.

Finally append the generated sentence to the sentence string to be 
returned to the user

commit_list.message:
Split submitted number into groups of three digits

Take advantage of the python format function that formats integers into
a string where thousands, millions etc are separated with a comma. Once 
formatted correctly the split function with a comma as the delimiting 
character get the groups almost how we want them.

e.g. 12345 —> ’12,345’ —> [’12’,’345’]

edina/Curious-Edinburgh/#40 Capture domain and http protocol values

If a launch URL is used the domain and optional http protocol values are 
extracted from the URL and used to create a new API endpoint to use with
the app.

Launch url takes the form:

`curious-edinburgh://DOMAIN?tour=TOUR_NAME&protocol=PROTOCOL_TYPE`

i.e.

`curious-edinburgh://curiousedinburgh.org?tour=Science&protocol=secure`

The `protocol` query string item is optional and can be either `secure` 
or `insecure`. However, any value other than `secure` results in the API 
endpoint url being prefixed with `http://`. If `secure` then the API
endpoint url is prefixed with `https://`.

commit_list.message:
Use column aliases for ‘url’ columns in database

Django REST Framework uses ‘url’ to link to instances of resources so if 
any model contains a column named ‘url’ the wrong value is populated for
the magic ‘url’ value.

By using the ‘db_column’ attribute for the field in the model definition
this can be circumvented.

Add YamJam to protect sensitive information

that we aren’t publishing any sensitive information such as database 
credentials or Django’s secret key when checking in code.

in a YAML file in the project directory. <http://yamjam.readthedocs.org>

commit_list.message:
edina/crowdsurvey#53: Create RecordGeometry class for representing Record.geometry

This is mappable so can use ObjectMapper to ingest and serialise JSON and
used the CoordinateTransform class to facilitate this.

This class should be extended to support the MGLAnnotation protocol so
we can add annotations to the map view that are associated to a specific
record. This allows us to navigate back to record instances to edit them.

* geojson elements - to define the survey location (currently a polygon
                     describing the bounding box for the survey)
